				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{{{{{\text{D}}}_{{{\text{ye}}}}}{{\varepsilon }_{{{\text{AB}}}}}}}{{{\text{AB}}}} = \frac{{{{A}_{{{\text{Dye}}}}}{{\varepsilon }_{{{\text{AB}}}}}}}{{({{A}_{{{\text{AB}}}}} - {{A}_{{{\text{Dye}}}}}{\text{CF}}){{\varepsilon }_{{{\text{Dye}}}}}}},$$\end{document}where DyeεAB/AB is the sought number of dye molecules per an antibody molecule, ADye is the optical density of the sample at the wavelength of the absorption maximum of the dye, AAB is the optical density of the sample at the wavelength of the absorption maximum of the proteins (280 nm), εAB is the molar extinction coefficient of the antibody at the wavelength of 280 nm (for IgG, 210 000), εDye is the molar extinction coefficient of the dye at the wavelength of the absorption maximum (for FITC, 72 000 M–1 cm–1), and CF280 is the correction factor for the dye at the wavelength of 280 nm.

